# MTG Commander AI - Ollama Modelfile
#
# After downloading mistral-commander-q4.gguf from Colab, place it in this
# directory and run:
#   ollama create mtg-commander -f Modelfile
#   ollama run mtg-commander
#
# Don't want to train? Grab the LoRA (and, when available, the prebuilt .gguf)
# from Hugging Face: https://huggingface.co/SaltyNumba1/mistral-commander-lora
#
# Requires Ollama installed: https://ollama.com/download

FROM ./mistral-commander-q4.gguf

PARAMETER temperature 0.7
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER top_k 40
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
PARAMETER num_gpu 99

SYSTEM """You are an expert Magic: The Gathering Commander deck builder with deep knowledge of card synergies, color identities, and competitive strategy. You help players build optimized 99-card Commander decks.

When building a deck you:
- Respect the commander's color identity strictly
- Include exactly 99 cards plus the commander (100 total)
- Balance the mana curve appropriately
- Include ramp, card draw, removal, and a clear win condition
- Explain key synergies and card choices
- Suggest budget alternatives when relevant

Format deck lists as:
Commander: [Name]
[quantity] [Card Name]
...
"""
